# UI Requirements (Universal)

What must be true of any UI regardless of toolkit. Repo-specific bindings, theme package, and widget inventory live in project `ui_requirements.instructions.md`.

Implementation detail files: `ui_code.instructions.md`, `ui_aesthetics.instructions.md`, `ui_testing.instructions.md`.

## Non-Negotiables

| #   | Rule                                                                                                                                                        |
| --- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1   | Keyboard / mouse / wheel / tablet input through a **remappable binding registry** — no hard-coded `Qt.MouseButton.*` or bare `QShortcut(...)` at call sites |
| 2   | Colors, fonts, metrics from **theme tokens** — no hex literals or `QColor("#...")` in widget code                                                           |
| 3   | Widgets are **thin shells** — business logic in non-UI modules, not in `_on_click` handlers                                                                 |
| 4   | Every renderable surface has a mandatory visual regression test (`@pytest.mark.gui` + screenshot where applicable)                                          |
| 5   | Defaults centralized in module `actions.py` / `default_theme.py` (or shared theme builtins) — no scattered inline defaults                                  |
| 6   | Actions/tokens **discoverable via registry** so prefs/editor surfaces them; consumers opt in to overrides only                                              |
| 7   | Every action reachable without a mouse                                                                                                                      |
| 8   | Expensive fullscreen/large-area fills GPU-first when GPU rendering is available; CPU only for validation/fallback/export                                    |
| 9   | Shader source in module-local `shaders/` — not embedded in Python except tiny fixtures                                                                      |
| 10  | Draw parameters affecting GPU output passed explicitly to shaders (uniforms/buffers/constants)                                                              |
| 11  | **Lookup before create** — scan existing shared widget inventory before writing new UI                                                                      |
| 12  | **Generic when ≥2 modules** — promote reusable widgets to shared package root early                                                                         |
| 13  | **Promote immediately** when a second module needs a module-local widget                                                                                    |
| 14  | **Canvas-embedded widgets stay canvas-blind** — adapter wiring lives outside the widget class                                                               |

## Bubble-Up vs Re-Declaration

Child registers its actions/tokens; parent registry discovers them. Re-declaration is **opt-in for overrides**, never mandatory pass-through.

## Accessibility Floor

- Body text contrast ≥ 4.5:1; large text / UI chrome ≥ 3:1 (WCAG AA)
- Visible focus indicators on interactive elements
- Respect OS reduced-motion / reduced-transparency when exposed

## Forbidden

- ❌ Hard-coded colors in widget code → theme tokens
- ❌ `if event.button() == Qt.LeftButton:` → binding registry
- ❌ `QShortcut("Ctrl+S", ...)` without a registered action
- ❌ File I/O, network, or heavy computation inside widgets
- ❌ Theme that changes layout topology or behavior
- ❌ CPU-only fullscreen procedural overlays after GPU proves faster
- ❌ New widgets without checking existing inventory
- ❌ Hidden shader defaults for values already owned by Python/theme config
